Students enter the subject with your own idea or concept design. The principles of design thinking and service design are introduced and the opportunity to apply them is given. The subject teaches students to develop your ideas using creative thinking techniques and design thinking principles. During the course, the original idea becomes a developed and structured idea, which is thoroughly thought out and presented to others. In addition, students learn to present their ideas convincinglyObjectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the subject is to give the participant an in-depth understanding of the idea development process and techniques. The subject develops creative problem-solving skills and introduces various tools for idea generation and development.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student: *has an overview of the concepts of idea development and applies them in the context of design thinking; *uses creative thinking techniques for problem solving and knows how to generate ideas; *applies creative thinking in solving practical problems and finds innovative solutions; * can present his/her/their ideas convincingly
